<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFB56A0AFF5693321ADEBD4B" pageId="78" pageNumber="836" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB56A0AFF5693321ADEBD4B" blockId="78.[166,1376,716,1816]" pageId="78" pageNumber="836">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFB56A0AFF5693321C0FBEBE" bold="true" box="[170,527,1387,1420]" pageId="78" pageNumber="836">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Large False Serotine appears to be forest-dependent, and it is suspected that its population has declined by more than 30% in the last 15 years, inferred from deforestation rates, and this level of decline will continue for the next 15 years. Habitat loss due to logging, plantations, agriculture, and forestfires is a major threat. It occurs in Sapagaya Forest Reserve and Tabin Widlife Reserve in Borneo, Taman Negara and Krau Wildlife Reserve in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB56A0AFE3C90391C37BD4B" box="[448,567,1632,1657]" name="Malaysia" pageId="78" pageNumber="836">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, and Kaeng Krachan National Park in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB56A0AFBA490391ADABD4B" box="[1112,1242,1632,1657]" name="Thailand" pageId="78" pageNumber="836">Thailand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
